EDIT [(line munber)] [(basic program)]
 edit currently loaded basic program

OPTIONS:
 (line number)   = an optional integer, the program line number N, not the Nth line
 (basic program) = if given, that will be edited instead of the currently loaded program

EXAMPLES:
 EDIT 9 autoexec-orig.bas
 EDIT 1000
 EDIT

NOTES:
 to set the editor, "export EDITOR=/usr/bin/vim.tiny" in '/etc/profile'

RELATED:
 INFO,LIST,LOAD,NEW

